messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 6/13/2002 8:58:51 AM Pacific Daylight Time, ... Our first phone number was Geneva 83885. You dialed GE83885 -- but all the numbers had words
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 6/13/2002 8:58:51 AM Pacific Daylight Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:


>
> I must have been VERY young, but I can remember actually getting our first
> phone. It was a princess style with a light up dial and the number was
> 714-539-4843. I can't remember the last few numbers we've had but that one
> has stuck with me always

Our first phone number was Geneva 83885. You dialed GE83885 -- but all the
numbers had words at the beginning like that.

The local cab company was Garfield 83885. It was on all the cabs, driving all
over town. I knew our phone number from listening to my parents say: "NO -
this is GENEVA 83885 not GARFIELD 83885 and we aren't the taxi company."
Sometimes people would argue and my dad would finally say, "Okay, we'll send
a cab now," and just hang up.

-pamS
